# ==========================================================================
# Libraries
#
# A Library is a top-level Python package.  Operators belong to libraries
# via their dotted FQN (the resolver splits on the first dot).
#
# When the pip package name differs from the Python import name, declare
# it with ``has package``.  Libraries where they match (e.g. "openrouter")
# don't need a ``has package`` entry — the resolver falls back to the
# import name.
#
# Submodule hierarchy uses ``is subclass of`` to model nesting:
#   sklearn.preprocessing is subclass of sklearn
# This lets operators like sklearn.preprocessing.StandardScaler resolve
# imports naturally from their FQN.
# ==========================================================================

# ---- Libraries ----
sklearn is a Library; has package scikit-learn
keras is a Library; has package tensorflow[keras]
cv2 is a Library; has package opencv-python
PIL is a Library; has package Pillow
bs4 is a Library; has package beautifulsoup4
openrouter is a Library
pandas is a Library
numpy is a Library
trust is a Library

# ---- OpenRouter module structure ----
# The operator FQN openrouter.chat.completion is a semantic name.
# The actual Python class is openrouter.OpenRouter.
# The is_subclass_of relationship tells the resolver which Python class
# to instantiate when the FQN doesn't resolve as a direct import path.
openrouter.chat.completion is subclass of openrouter.OpenRouter
